         <abstract>
            <p>Housing will be one of the strongest growth industries of the 1970's. Within the overall housing industry, the modular housing segment is on the verge of a period of exceptionally rapid growth: The Federal Government is now actively encouraging this industry. The demand for new housing is simply overwhelming and the conventional homebuilding industry cannot satisfy this demand. The trend of rising costs in the homebuilding industry point toward modular housing as the only answer for a vast segment of the market. And finally, consumer reluctance to accept modular housing will gradually be overcome by better quality, lower cost, and the favorable publicity that will accompany government programs such as Operation Breakthrough.</p>
          </abstract>
